etty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDisney%20recruiter%20Jason%20Gibson%20shared%20the%20keys%20to%20getting%20a%20job%20at%20Disney%20World.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESuccessful%20applicants%20are%20strong%20communicators%20who%20are%20positive%20and%20engaging.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBeing%20a%20big%20Disney%20fan%20isn't%20required%2C%20but%20enthusiasm%20can%20help%20guests%20feel%20at%20home.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-costs-save-money-vacation-budget-lightning-lanes-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDisney%20World%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20dream%20for%20many%20lifelong%20Mouse%20House%20fans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20these%20Disney%20die-hards%2C%20recruiters%20are%20like%20genies.%20One%20such%20dream-maker%20is%20Jason%20Gibson%2C%20a%20lifelong%20Disney%20fan%20who's%20worked%20at%20the%20parks%20for%20over%2027%20years%2C%20including%20nearly%20two%20decades%20as%20a%20recruiter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Gibson%20outlined%20how%20to%20get%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-college-program-interview-careers-tips-advice-disney-world-job-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20at%20Disney%20World%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20discussed%20topics%20like%20the%20types%20of%20questions%20applicants%20are%20asked%20and%20how%20they%20should%20prepare%20for%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20recruiters%20are%20incredibly%20transparent%2C%26quot%3B%20Gibson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20he%20said%20Disney%20recruiters%20tell%20many%20applicants%20whether%20they're%20getting%20a%20job%20offer%20before%20they%20end%20their%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b71c0962-5b51-4ecd-a1d7-16d3b814c753%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20apply%20to%20and%20interview%20at%20Disney%20World%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDisney%20World%20hopefuls%20who%20find%20an%20open%20role%20on%20the%20Mouse%20House's%20job%20board%20should%20first%20carefully%20review%20the%20job%20description%20and%20responsibilities%20to%20make%20sure%20they're%20a%20fit%2C%20Gibson%20said.%20If%20so%2C%20they%20should%20apply%20and%20indicate%20their%20potential%20availability.%20Those%20who%20can't%2C%20or%20won't%2C%20work%20on%20nights%20and%20weekends%20probably%20won't%20be%20a%20good%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20selected%20for%20an%20interview%2C%20applicants%20should%20be%20ready%20to%20answer%20questions%20about%20themselves%20and%20the%20specific%20role%20they%20applied%20for.%20They%20should%20also%20be%20prepared%20to%20explain%20any%20significant%20gaps%20in%20their%20work%20history%2C%20if%20they%20have%20any%2C%20since%20that%20otherwise%20could%20be%20a%20red%20flag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDisney%20applicants%20can%20win%20over%20the%20recruiter%20by%20sharing%20their%20life%20story%20in%20a%20concise%20yet%20compelling%20way%2C%20Gibson%20said.%20Besides%20charming%20the%20interviewer%2C%20presenting%20a%20strong%20personal%20narrative%20shows%20that%20an%20applicant%20can%20communicate%20clearly%20and%20effectively%20with%20guests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20best%20advice%20I%20could%20give%20a%20candidate%20is%3A%20tell%20your%20story%2C%26quot%3B%20Gibson%20said.%20After%20all%2C%20he%20said%20that%20storytelling%20is%20Disney's%20backbone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApplicants%20should%20also%20be%20prepared%20to%20answer%20open-ended%20hypothetical%20questions%20based%20on%20scenarios%20they%20may%20face%20if%20hired%2C%20Gibson%20said.%20Those%20questions%20vary%20based%20on%20the%20role%2C%20though%20they%20could%20include%20scenarios%20about%20dealing%20with%20difficult%20guests%20or%20issues%20with%20coworkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ab5d0483-51ea-46d2-b860-1bf9d1ebac1b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Disney%20World%20recruiters%20want%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDisney%20World%20recruiters%20are%20looking%20for%20people%20wh